{{>_workflow-status}}

{{h2}}Issue Management

{{b}}Arguments{{b}}
- `--issue=issue-id` - Set new issue (openspec path or component)
- `--description="text"` - Set issue description
- `--tracking="TYPE ID"` - Set tracking (e.g. "JIRA GUIDE-123")
- `--queue=issue-id` - Queue an issue (openspec path or component)
- `--clear` - Remove current issue
- `--next` - Move next queued issue to current

> Only one of --clear, --next, or issue-id is valid.
> --description and --tracking can be used anytime.
> Validate phase restrictions before making changes.

{{h2}}Examples
- `{{#command}}issue{{/command}}{{#command-flags}}issue=openspec/changes/new-feature{{/command-flags}}`
- `{{#command}}issue{{/command}}{{#command-flags}}description=Fix validation bug{{/command-flags}}`
- `{{#command}}issue{{/command}}{{#command-flags}}tracking=JIRA PROJ-456{{/command-flags}}`
- `{{#command}}issue{{/command}}{{#command-flags}}clear{{/command-flags}}`
- `{{#command}}issue{{/command}}{{#command-flags}}next{{/command-flags}}`

